INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('276', '1', '2010-12-20 20:43:36', '2010-12-20 20:43:36', 'Due to popular demand we established the international department of queens park real estates, tailored to adapt to the economic climate of the different parts of the world and assist our current and potential clients sell or let their proprieties around the globe.\r\n\r\nOur aim is to assist homeowners and businesses irrespective of what part of the world they reside enter their properties in the global property market , hassle free and at the barest minimum cost : at qpre we believe that the more people see and hear about it the more you are spoiled for choice which enables you achieve the best price for your property.\r\n\r\nWe advertise your property on all major marketing sites in the world there by giving your property maximum exposure.\r\n\r\nWe leave you in control of your property from advertisement ( choice of words, picture and viewing s) to the sale 24hrs 7 day a week who best sells the property if not the owner; you get instant messages from all enquiries made on your property and can arrange viewings at you convenience.\r\n\r\nAdvertisement is very quick and easy to do; your property becomes live with 24hrs of completing the transaction.\r\nOne off payment is required and you do not need to pay us any completion when you eventually sell or let your property( this depends on the package you require)\r\nWe are a One stop shop or all your property needs.\r\n\r\nYou property could be advertised up to 12 months and this gives you more than enough time to find a suitable buyer for your home. \r\n\r\nWe have a teams that understand your local language.\r\n', 'International', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '155-revision-5', '', '', '2010-12-20 20:43:36', '2010-12-20 20:43:36', '', '155', 'http://www.queensparkrealestates.co.uk/2010/12/20/155-revision-5/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('250', '1', '2010-12-04 13:15:30', '2010-12-04 13:15:30', 'Queens Park Landlord Services\r\n[singlepic id=6 float=]\r\nWe can tailor our services to your particular requirements, however:\r\n\r\n	We Guarantee you don’t pay us a penny and your not tied in unless we find you a tenant your happy with (no upfront fees at all)\r\n	Rent guarantee on your property for 6 or 12 months is available\r\n	We aim to keep our fees one of the lowest of any quality agent in the area\r\n	We only focus on Lettings and Management\r\n	We have a policy to always be upfront and honest\r\n	We take advantage of all the latest technology and tools to let your property quickly\r\n	The longest opening hours: In response to the demands of living and working we have found that many people cannot make viewings within most of our competitors working hours. We strive to make viewings and valuations at a time that is convenient to you up to 8.30pm, 7 days a week.\r\n	Quality 3rd party referencing to insure you get impartial checks to insure the highest caliber of tenants for your property.\r\n\r\nLet Only Service\r\nQueens Park will provide the following services\r\n\r\n\r\n	To prepare details for the purpose of marketing. To advertise where we consider to be the most effective according to market conditions and historic advertising response levels.\r\n	To negotiate an acceptable monthly rent and term between the landlord and the tenant. To carry out referencing on the tenant including credit checking.\r\n	To prepare an assured shorthold tenancy agreement for the monthly rent and term agreed in accordance with. To collect 1 calendar month’s rent in advance and the damage deposit in cleared funds\r\n	To organise a schedule of condition. (Full inventory available)\r\n	To forward all monies to the landlord via either bank transfer or cheque minus our agreed fee.\r\n\r\nFull Management Service\r\nQueens Park will provide the following services\r\n\r\n\r\n	To prepare details for the purpose of marketing. To advertise where we consider to be the most effective according to market conditions and historic advertising response levels\r\n	To negotiate an acceptable monthly rent and term between the landlord and the tenant. To carry out reference on the tenant including credit checking\r\n	To prepare an assured shorthold tenancy agreement for the monthly rent and term agreed in accordance. To collect 1 calendar month’s rent in advance and the damage deposit in cleared funds. To provide an inventory of the property and check the tenant in including taking meter readings\r\n	To organise a full Inventory, and do a property handover with the tenant\r\n	To respond to all disrepair reported to us from the tenant during the duration of the tenancy. To inform the landlord of any such reports, and obtain quotes so that action may be taken.\r\n	To comply with all reasonable instructions received from the landlord in relation to the management of the property in accordance to the principles of good management.\r\n	To carry out a check out once the tenant has vacated the property and advise the landlord of any discrepancies with the schedule of condition / inventory and state of the property.\r\n	To forward the rent to the landlord minus our agreed fee on a monthly basis. The landlord can choose to receive this either by bank transfer or cheque.\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '250', '', '', '2011-03-14 14:08:54', '2011-03-14 14:08:54', '', '0', 'http://www.queensparkrealestates.co.uk/?p=250', '2', 'nav_menu_item', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('251', '1', '2010-12-04 13:15:30', '2010-12-04 13:15:30', 'Information for Vendors\r\n[singlepic id=8 float=]\r\n\r\nIt is an unfortunate fact that one in four sales in the UK fail to complete. But we continue to take action to reduce that figure. Whilst many agents don’t have this facility, we have a team of dedicated Move Managers covering our branch network. Their commitment is to move the sale on to a quick conclusion. Experienced in both the legal process and customer service, these office-based managers offer one of the facets of our service which is most highly regarded by our clients.\r\n\r\nStatistics show the innovation has managed to reduce the time a sale takes to progress from ‘under offer’ to a successful exchange of contracts, a tremendous benefit to our clients. \r\n\r\nUseful and time saving pointers\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nInstruct your solicitor early on so they can begin some of the procedures and prepare some of the documentation – it saves valuable time once a buyer has been found for your home. Not got a solicitor? We can appoint one to act for you.\r\nAdvise your solicitor of your mortgage account number and name of your mortgage lender so they can obtain the deeds in advance; this can save, literally, weeks at a later stage.\r\nComplete the fixtures and fittings enquiry form provided and return it to your solicitor.\r\nIf the property is jointly owned, both parties need to agree to it being sold and that the price is acceptable. Your solicitor will need to know the details of any agreements that you have.\r\nIf the property you are selling is a flat or leasehold you will need to ensure that your ground rent and management service charges are up to date.\r\n\r\n\r\nCall 0207 372 5950 for a free valuation or email sales@Queens Park.co.uk\r\n\r\n\r\nValuation – Getting the price right\r\n\r\nIn a stable or declining market, an overpriced property simply will not sell; there are too many other homes with similar benefits which are more competitively priced.\r\n\r\nWouldn’t it be wonderful if home-owners could set the price for their own homes? They would simply add up the original cost, plus any improvements and add an appropriate profit. \r\n\r\nMaybe the estate agent could determine the price in consultation with the owner? However, the fact is that neither the owner’s investment, nor their economic conditions and desires, nor the estate agent’s opinion has anything to do with the market value of a home. Ultimately it is the buyer who sets the price; as until a buyer commits to purchase at a specific price, the value of a home remains undetermined.\r\n\r\nWhilst it is the buyer who determines the selling price, it is the owner, in consultation with the estate agent, who sets the asking price.\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\nMarketing Your Home With Technology\r\n\r\n\r\nSelling your home via the internet\r\nE-mail updates the minute a property goes live.\r\n\r\n\r\nOver 80% of buyers are updated via e-mail about latest listed homes as they become available. So, when we sell your property, details reach our database of applicants in record time, often within 3hrs hours of the property coming onto the market.\r\n\r\nVirtual Tours and floorplans\r\nVirtual Tours and floorplans of most properties are available to view on the Queens Park website. These save time and inconvenience for you and your potential buyers. Our research shows that homes with Virtual Tours produce high quality viewings, which can result in significantly less people needing to be shown your home before a sale is achieved. Our office be able to provide full details for you including a live demonstration. Better people providing the best service Our biggest asset is our staff. Queens Park attracts and selects the best in the business and employs more staff to be at your service. This ensures that we respond to your needs as quickly and efficiently as possible. Our teams are highly trained professionals whose local knowledge and expertise ensure the service you receive is of the highest standard. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '251', '', '', '2011-03-14 14:08:54', '2011-03-14 14:08:54', '', '0', 'http://www.queensparkrealestates.co.uk/?p=251', '3', 'nav_menu_item', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('252', '1', '2010-12-04 13:15:30', '2010-12-04 13:15:30', 'Tenants Information\r\n[singlepic id=7  float=]\r\nAt Queens Park we believe that it is essential to communicate effectively and will always offer honest impartial advice to our tenants throughout the tenancy.\r\n\r\nWe are able to offer a professional service to individuals, companies and relocation agencies.\r\n\r\nIf you are interested in renting through Queens Park please call on 0207 372 5950 or e-mail : info@Queens Park.co.uk\r\nRequirements\r\nBefore you rent a property through Queens Park, we will take up references on behalf of the landlord which will normally include an employer’s reference, any former landlord and an additional credit reference. Where a tenant is unable to meet the required income or credit checks, you will be asked to provide a Guarantor to underwrite any rent liabilities.\r\n\r\nYou will be required to pay a deposit against damages together with 4 week’s rent in advance. Many tenants are concerned about their security deposit. By renting through us, your deposit will be protected by the Tenancy Deposit Scheme (TDS) operated by an independent body which ensures that only legitimate claims are made against deposits. The TDS also offers a dispute resolution service for cases where parties are unable to reach an agreement.\r\nDocumentation\r\nOur tenancy agreements have been carefully drafted using plain English and will clearly state what type of tenancy you have and which party carries which responsibility. It is important that you read your tenancy agreement thoroughly. If you are unsure of anything, one of our team will be happy to assist you.\r\n\r\nAll documentation will be carefully explained to ensure you fully understand the legal implications before signing the tenancy agreement and committing to the tenancy.\r\n\r\nIt is important that you attend the inventory check-in so that can agree to any amendments. We recommend you keep the check-in and your tenancy agreement in a safe place as these form the basis for any claims for damages at the end of the tenancy.\r\nLooking after the property\r\nYour landlord is liable for most maintenance and repairs to the property but it is your duty to notify us of any problems you notice. Routine housework such as cleaning, gardening, renewal of light bulbs will be your responsibility.\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '252', '', '', '2011-03-14 14:08:54', '2011-03-14 14:08:54', '', '0', 'http://www.queensparkrealestates.co.uk/?p=252', '4', 'nav_menu_item', '', '0');
